      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\nimport math\n\ndef calculate_position(a, e, i, Omega, omega, nu):\n    # Convert angles from degrees to radians\n    i = math.radians(i)\n    Omega = math.radians(Omega)\n    omega = math.radians(omega)\n    nu = math.radians(nu)\n    \n    # Calculate the distance from the central body\n    r = (a * (1 - e**2)) / (1 + e * math.cos(nu))\n    \n    # Calculate the position in the orbital plane\n    x_orbital = r * math.cos(nu)\n    y_orbital = r * math.sin(nu)\n    \n    # Calculate the position in the inertial frame\n    x = (math.cos(Omega) * math.cos(omega) - math.sin(Omega) * math.sin(omega) * math.cos(i)) * x_orbital - (math.sin(Omega) * math.cos(omega) + math.cos(Omega) * math.sin(omega) * math.cos(i)) * y_orbital\n    y = (math.cos(Omega) * math.sin(omega) + math.sin(Omega) * math.cos(omega) *",
